data.title: Contrast-Enhanced MR Imaging of Brain Lesions: A Large-Scale Intraindividual Crossover Comparison of Gadobenate Dimeglumine versus Gadodiamide
data.meta_description: Glioblastoma with recurrent disease. This 55-year-old woman shows more conspicuous enhancement (arrows) in the right posterior temporal lobe with gadobenate dimeglumine than gadodiamide for both SE and GRE sequences. Although there are differences in angulation, changes were confirmed by review of all adjacent sections.
